And if you understand that symbiosis, you'll understand why the "behind-the-scenes" filter is compelling. It predicts the same legislative actions. But it also reminds us that the people in power don't care what the people really think, so long as they stay in power. 7/

The reality is that whatever is "taboo" is the thing that gets the press coverage, because that's whatever is most likely to generate clicks. CNN is eager to publish a headline like "Joe Manchin just *totally* screwed Democrats". Gotta get that green. 6/

I'm certainly not excusing the R Establishment either, because I fully believe there are movers and shakers behind those scenes, too. But the Rs aren't in power right now so their "moving and shaking" is going to be somewhat limited. 5/
